# Force LF line endings repo-wide. Without this, Windows clones with
# `core.autocrlf=true` (the default on git-for-windows) rewrite every
# file's line endings on checkout, then re-stage them as "changed" when
# any unrelated edit lands — polluting every PR diff with whitespace
# noise. Pinning eol=lf ensures the file on disk matches what's in git.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary files we don't want LF-normalised.
*.png    binary
*.jpg    binary
*.jpeg   binary
*.gif    binary
*.ico    binary
*.sqlite binary
*.db     binary
